> Yes.. i've heard the "do you want to sit by your server" toss. but not
> all machines are webservers where processes are throwaway httpd's. Think
> credit card transaction processing.
Thats transaction based. Those guys expect to have crashes and they expect
to guarantee no replication occurs. To do that requires you system is already
capable of handling application, system, network and hardware failures
